    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a53418ad_22d21e4f",
        "filename": "status/go/find_breaks/failure_groups.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 98,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-05T13:57:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I haven\u0027t figured out how this whole thing works on an ongoing basis.  ie, we run this every minute or so, and... what?  We may end up with new or modified FailureGroups which need to be reconciled with the ones we\u0027ve already found (and possibly sent alerts for). \n\nAs for this particular rule, I just realized that it\u0027s not quite right.  If the current window is [b, c, d, e, f], and we have these failures:\n1. [a, b, c, d]\n2.         [c]\n\nThey *could* have the same cause (c), but we\u0027d assign f1.brokeIn \u003d (-1, -1) and f2.brokeIn \u003d (1, 2) which would be rejected by this rule.  Changed such that the first failing task in the window gets assigned to brokeIn.  We may incorrectly associate previously-broken bots with the wrong commit, but that\u0027s better than not matching when we could have.",
      "parentUuid": "6912792f_6f49153c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 96,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 98,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "revId": "dd2689b65003958f3d15e5adddf3c74e1556e297",
