      "writtenOn": "2017-04-03T19:33:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t understand this.\n\nIt seems you are trying to find all possible groupings of failures, since whether or not maybeMerge merges depends on the order of previous merges. However, in order to do that, you would need to iterate over all possible permutations of failures, since B.maybeMerge(A).maybeMerge(C) could give different results from B.maybeMerge(C).maybeMerge(A).\n\nAlso, it seems like rather than generating all possible groupings, we really want to partition failures into groups, i.e. no two groups should contain the same failure. However, the deduplication below doesn\u0027t achieve that -- it only deduplicates identical groups.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 151,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 157,
        "endChar": 3
      },
