      "writtenOn": "2017-04-05T13:57:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO:  We have to start somewhere.  I find it difficult to write a full design doc without some exploratory work.\n\nThe overall goal is to present the sheriff with an alert, to the effect of: \"These bots (or tests) \u003cx, y, z\u003e are failing because of this (or these) commit(s): \u003ca, b, c\u003e.  Click [here] to revert, Click [here] to file a bug\"\n\nThere are a lot of steps to distill all of the information we have (perf regressions, untriaged/failing gold images, failed/mishap tasks) into that type of alert.  My goal with this CL was to take just the tasks part and start figuring out how we could narrow down the cause of failure using only the task history, with the understanding that things like distinguishing what actually failed (eg. crash vs failed test) would come later.  FWIW I kind of imagined an overlay on top of the current status page which highlighted the failure groups for quicker visual distinction, though I don\u0027t think I\u0027d actually follow through with that, due to low value per effort spent.",
      "parentUuid": "09f13fe4_327c63a7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 10,
